# HTML5 TV Keycodes by Platform

Keycode mappings for all HTML5-based smart TV platforms. Values sourced from the velope PAL platform implementations (`velope/ott-platform-*/`).

The PAL maps **numeric DOM keycodes** to **logical key names**. App code should only use logical names; the PAL resolves the correct keycode per platform at runtime.

---

## Logical key names (KeyType)

Defined in `ott-core` (`PlatformModels.d.ts`):

`Left` | `Right` | `Up` | `Down` | `Back` | `MediaPlay` | `MediaPause` | `MediaPlayPause` | `MediaFastForward` | `MediaRewind` | `MediaTrackNext` | `MediaTrackPrevious` | `Exit`

**Note:** `Enter` is not in the core `KeyType` union but is used by the Run3TV platform and by the Lightning UI component layer (`onEnter`, `_handleEnter`). Standard DOM keycode 13 (Enter/Return) is handled by the framework's input system for most platforms without an explicit PAL mapping.

---

## Navigation keycodes (arrows, Enter, Back)

The keys every TV app needs. This is the first table to consult.

| Key | Samsung Tizen | LG webOS | Vizio | Fire TV / Android TV | Browser (dev) | Run3TV |
|-----|:------------:|:--------:|:-----:|:-------------------:|:-------------:|:------:|
| **Up** | 38 | 38 | 38 | 38 | 38 | *(dynamic)* |
| **Down** | 40 | 40 | 40 | 40 | 40 | *(dynamic)* |
| **Left** | 37 | 37 | 37 | 37 | 37 | *(dynamic)* |
| **Right** | 39 | 39 | 39 | 39 | 39 | *(dynamic)* |
| **Enter** | 13 | 13 | 13 | 13 | 13 | *(dynamic)* |
| **Back** | **10009** | **461** | **8** | **8** *(verify)* | — | *(dynamic)* / 461 |
| **Exit** | — | — | **27** | — | — | **27** |

Arrow keys (37–40) and Enter (13) are **standard DOM keycodes** and are the same on every Chromium-based TV. **Back is the key that differs by platform** — this is the primary reason the PAL exists for key handling.

