| **38** | Arrow Up | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | **Up** | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | — |
| **39** | Arrow Right | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | **Right** | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | — |
| **40** | Arrow Down | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | **Down** | *(browser default)* | *(browser default)* | — |
| **70** | F (keyboard) | — | — | — | — | **MediaFastForward** | — |
| **80** | P (keyboard) | — | — | — | — | **MediaPlayPause** | — |
| **82** | R (keyboard) | — | — | — | — | **MediaRewind** | — |
| **412** | MediaRewind (HID) | **MediaRewind** | **MediaRewind** | **MediaRewind** | — | — | — |
| **413** | MediaStop (HID) | — | — | **MediaPlayPause** | — | — | — |
| **415** | MediaPlay (HID) | **MediaPlayPause** | **MediaPlay** | **MediaPlayPause** | — | — | — |
| **417** | MediaFastForward (HID) | **MediaFastForward** | **MediaFastForward** | **MediaFastForward** | — | — | — |
| **418** | MediaTrackNext (HID) | — | — | **MediaTrackNext** | — | — | — |
| **419** | MediaTrackPrevious (HID) | — | — | **MediaTrackPrevious** | — | — | — |
| **461** | webOS Back | — | **Back** | — | — | — | **Back** *(fallback)* |
| **10009** | Tizen Back | **Back** | — | — | — | — | — |
| **10252** | Tizen MediaPlayPause | *(registered)* | — | — | — | — | — |

*(browser default)* = Arrow keys (37–40) and Enter (13) are handled by the framework's input layer (e.g. Lightning's `useFocusManager` or the Lightning 2 `StageApplication`) without an explicit PAL keyMapping entry. They use standard DOM keycodes that are consistent across all Chromium-based TVs.

*(framework)* = Enter (13) is handled at the framework level, not in the PAL keyMapping.

*(dynamic)* = Run3TV reads keycodes from `window.fmw.device.deviceInput` at runtime and maps `Select`/`Ok` → Enter, `Return`/`Back` → Back.

*(registered)* = Tizen registers media keys via `tizen.tvinputdevice.registerKeyBatch()` during platform init (`MediaPause`, `MediaPlay`, `MediaFastForward`, `MediaRewind`).

